quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  4,51,"Did you not consider those who were given a portion from the book? They believe in idols and false deities and say about those who do not believe, \"These (disbelievers) are better guided on the (right) way than those who believe"
  4,52,"Those are the persons whom God has cursed and he whom God curses, you will never find for him a helper"
  4,53,"Or have they a share in the kingdom? Then in that case they would not have given (to other) people, even a speck on a date stone"
  4,54,"Or are they jealous of the people on account of that which God has given them from His grace? Then We indeed gave to the family (progeny) of Abraham, the book and the wisdom, and We gave them a great kingdom. We gave them a great kingdom"
  4,55,"So among them were (some) who believed in it and among them were (others) who turned away from it, and hell is sufficient for (their) burning"
  4,56,"Those who do not believe in Our signs, We will certainly make them enter the fire, as their skins are thoroughly burned, We will change them for other (new) skins that they may taste the punishment, God is certainly Mighty, Wise"
  4,57,"And those who believe and do righteous works We will make them enter the gardens beneath which rivers flow, they will stay therein for ever, for them there will be clean mates therein and We will make them enter a shady shade"
  4,58,"God certainly commands you that you should return the trusts (deposited by people), to their owners, and when you judge between people then you should judge with justice. That with which God admonishes you is certainly excellent, God is certainly Hearing, Seeing"
  4,59,"O you who believe ! obey God and obey the messenger and those who are in authority among you. And if you have a dispute in anything, then refer it to God and the messenger if you are believers in God and the period hereafter"